We can distribute and combine like terms to determine which choice matches the expression given, $21-6x$.

Choice (A):

$\begin{align}
5-2(8-3x)&=5-2(8)-2(-3x) \\\\
&=5-16+6x \\\\
&=\redD{-11+6x}
\end{align}$

Choice (B): 

$\begin{align}
6+3(5-2x)&=6+3(5)+3(-2x) \\\\
&=6+15-6x \\\\
&=\greenD{21-6x}
\end{align}$

Choice (C):

$\begin{align}
25-(4-6x)&=25-1(4)-1(-6x)\\\\
&=25-4+6x \\\\
&=\redD{21+6x}
\end{align}$

Choice (D):

$\begin{align}
3(4-2x)-9&=3(4)+3(-2x)-9 \\\\
&=12-6x-9 \\\\
&=\redD{3-6x}
\end{align}$

Choice (E): 

$\begin{align}
7(3-2x)-8x&=7(3)+7(-2x)-8x \\\\
&=21-14x-8x \\\\
&=\redD{21-22x}
\end{align}$

**$6+3(5-2x)$ is equivalent to $21-6x$.**
